OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWhat a coffee ad reveals   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fabout transphobia in India 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, It's hard to not be accepted for who   
OL,6, you are. It's harder still if the ones 
OL,7, not accepting you are your parents.    
OL,9,FAnd that's why a recent Starbucks ad   
OL,10,Fabout parents rekindling ties with     
OL,11,Ftheir adult daughter - a transgender   
OL,12,Fwoman - has touched a chord with many. 
OL,14,FIn the ad, the couple meet their       
OL,15,Fdaughter in a coffee shop after being  
OL,16,Festranged from her for years and the   
OL,17,Ffather shows his acceptance of her     
OL,18,Fdecision to transition by addressing   
OL,19,Fher by her chosen name, Arpita, instead
OL,20,Fof Arpit.                              
